  <!-- BACK BOILER SECTION, UNIQUE ST HELENS CONTENT -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="pf-section-label">ST HELENS SPECIALIST SERVICE</span>
      <h2>Back Boiler Replacement in St Helens. What You Need to Know.</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Back boilers, the gas boilers fitted behind gas fires, remain more common in St Helens than almost anywhere in Merseyside. Many WA10 Victorian terraces still run on back boiler systems installed in the 1970s and 1980s. Replacing one is not the same as a standard boiler swap.</p>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-red">
          <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Why Back Boilers Must Be Replaced</strong>
          <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">Back boilers installed before 1990 were designed with different combustion processes than modern condensing boilers and cannot match modern efficiency standards. Spare parts for back boilers have become increasingly difficult to source over the last decade, and many are now entirely obsolete. A back boiler running at 55 to 65% efficiency is costing you significantly more in gas bills than a modern A-rated condensing boiler would. More importantly, ageing back boiler systems can present carbon monoxide risks when heat exchangers begin to crack, a problem that is not always visible on external inspection.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">What a Back Boiler Replacement Involves</strong>
          <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0 0 0.75rem;line-height:1.65;">A back boiler replacement is a more involved job than a standard combi swap. The process typically involves removing the gas fire and surround, safely disconnecting and removing the back boiler from behind the chimney breast, capping the original flue in the chimney, deciding on the optimal position for the new boiler, cutting a new flue route through an external wall, and replumbing the heating and hot water connections to the new boiler position. In WA10 and WA9 Victorian properties with original internal layouts, this often means working in narrow spaces with aged pipework that needs replacing as part of the installation. We carry out these jobs regularly across St Helens and know exactly what to plan for.</p>
          <div style="background:#fff7ed;border:1px solid #fed7aa;border-radius:var(--radius-sm);padding:0.75rem 1rem;">
            <p style="font-size:0.88rem;color:#78350f;margin:0;font-weight:600;">Free survey essential. Back boiler replacement prices vary significantly depending on the existing layout of your St Helens property. We always survey in person before quoting. Prices typically start from £2,500 fully completed.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-green">
          <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">The ECO4 Opportunity for Back Boiler Homes</strong>
          <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">Properties with back boilers are among the most likely to qualify for ECO4 funding, because the scheme specifically targets low-efficiency heating systems. If you live in WA10 or WA9 and your home still has a back boiler system, there is a realistic chance you may qualify for a fully funded replacement under ECO4. The eligibility criteria are broader than many people assume, you do not need to be on benefits to qualify in all circumstances. We assess ECO4 eligibility as a standard part of our free survey for St Helens properties with back boilers. It costs nothing to find out.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ST HELENS PROPERTY TYPES AND BOILERS -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="pf-section-label">LOCAL KNOWLEDGE</span>
      <h2>St Helens Property Types. Which Boiler Fits Each One.</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">St Helens has a distinct mix of housing built across five different periods. The right boiler depends on which era your home comes from and what heating system is currently in place.</p>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1.25rem;margin-top:2rem;">
        <div style="background:var(--white);border:1px solid var(--border);border-left:4px solid var(--orange);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:1.25rem;">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:0.75rem;align-items:center;margin-bottom:0.5rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <span style="background:var(--orange);color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:0.2rem 0.6rem;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:0.82rem;flex-shrink:0;">WA10 VICTORIAN TERRACES</span>
            <strong style="color:var(--navy);font-size:0.95rem;">Often back boiler or regular boiler. Combi possible with survey.</strong>
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;">Glass worker and industrial worker terraces built before 1914. Many still have back boilers or original gravity-fed systems. Some are on combi boilers already. Mains pressure varies significantly between streets. Survey essential before recommending boiler type.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background:var(--white);border:1px solid var(--border);border-left:4px solid var(--orange);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:1.25rem;">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:0.75rem;align-items:center;margin-bottom:0.5rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <span style="background:var(--orange);color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:0.2rem 0.6rem;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:0.82rem;flex-shrink:0;">WA11 HAYDOCK SEMIS</span>
            <strong style="color:var(--navy);font-size:0.95rem;">Typically combi or system boiler. 1950s to 1970s stock.</strong>
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;">Post-war semi-detached housing. End-of-life copper pipework and boilers common in this era. Most properties have adequate mains pressure for a combi. For 3-bedroom properties with one bathroom, a 28kW combi is typically correct. For larger Haydock houses, system boiler may be better value long term.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background:var(--white);border:1px solid var(--border);border-left:4px solid var(--orange);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:1.25rem;">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:0.75rem;align-items:center;margin-bottom:0.5rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <span style="background:var(--orange);color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:0.2rem 0.6rem;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:0.82rem;flex-shrink:0;">WA12 NEWTON-LE-WILLOWS</span>
            <strong style="color:var(--navy);font-size:0.95rem;">Mixed. Victorian near station vs modern estates.</strong>
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;">Newton-le-Willows has genuine property diversity. Victorian and Edwardian terraces close to Earlestown station have similar characteristics to WA10, back boilers possible, older systems. The modern private estates on the outskirts are typically 1990s onward and take a straight combi swap very cleanly. We confirm which applies to your specific property at the free survey.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background:var(--white);border:1px solid var(--border);border-left:4px solid var(--orange);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:1.25rem;">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:0.75rem;align-items:center;margin-bottom:0.5rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <span style="background:var(--orange);color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:0.2rem 0.6rem;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:0.82rem;flex-shrink:0;">WA9 WN5 VILLAGES</span>
            <strong style="color:var(--navy);font-size:0.95rem;">Older stock, vented cylinders common. Regular boiler often best.</strong>
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;">Billinge, Thatto Heath, Clock Face and surrounding mining community villages have a high proportion of older housing that was never updated to combi systems. Vented hot water cylinders and older regular boilers remain common. ECO4 eligibility rates are high in these areas. We attend properties across WN5 and WA9 regularly and understand the typical configurations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- SIGNS -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Signs Your St Helens Boiler Needs Replacing</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">If your boiler is over 10 years old or showing any of these signs, replacement is likely more cost-effective than continued repair.</p>
      <div class="pf-signs" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Your home still has a back boiler behind a gas fire</strong><p>Back boilers installed before 1990 are running at 55 to 65% efficiency at best, costing significantly more in gas bills than a modern A-rated boiler. Spare parts for back boilers are now largely obsolete. Replacement is rarely a question of if, it is a question of when.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Boiler over 10 to 12 years old</strong><p>Modern condensing boilers operate at over 90% efficiency. A pre-2010 boiler runs at 65 to 70%. The energy saving on gas bills alone will typically contribute to the installation cost within a few years.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Mounting repair costs</strong><p>In St Helens's older housing stock, where many boilers were fitted in the 1980s and 1990s, parts availability is declining and labour costs for specialist repairs are rising. If annual repair bills exceed £200 to £300, replacement pays for itself.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Yellow or orange flame</strong><p>A healthy boiler flame is blue. Yellow or orange indicates potential incomplete combustion and carbon monoxide risk. Stop using the boiler immediately. Call a <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Gas Safe engineer</a> or Cadent Gas on 0800 111 999 if you suspect a gas emergency.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Boiler shuts down frequently or loses pressure</strong><p>Frequent lockouts and pressure loss are symptoms of failing internal components. In a boiler over 12 years old, these issues rarely have a single fix, they signal the end of the system's reliable life.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>You have no Gas Safe or Benchmark certificate</strong><p>A boiler without documentation has no verified compliant installation. You have no warranty protection. If you are a landlord in St Helens, this also affects your ability to issue gas safety certificates.</p></div></div>
      </div>

      <div style="background:#f97316;border-radius:10px;padding:1.5rem;text-align:center;margin-top:2rem;">
        <p style="color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Still on a back boiler? You may qualify for a free replacement under ECO4. Book a free survey to find out.</p>
        <a href="tel:07399676656" class="btn btn-lg" style="background:#1a3a5c;color:#ffffff;box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(26,58,92,0.4);">CALL 07399 676656</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- WHAT IS INCLUDED -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What Is Included in Your St Helens Boiler Installation</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">No hidden extras. No surprise charges on invoice day. Every item below is included in your fully fitted price.</p>
      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>New boiler supplied and fitted</strong><p>Your chosen boiler from Worcester Bosch, Vaillant, Ideal or Baxi. Correctly sized for your specific St Helens property at the free survey, not a guess from a postcode.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>New smart controls and programmer</strong><p>New room thermostat and programmer installed and set up. Smart controls including Nest and Hive available. Required under <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/boiler-plus" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Boiler Plus regulations</a>.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Magnetic system filter</strong><p>Fitted to capture debris and magnetite before it reaches the new boiler. Required by Worcester Bosch and Vaillant to maintain manufacturer warranty. Non-negotiable on every installation.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>System flush and inhibitor</strong><p>Flushed and dosed to BS 7593 standard before the new boiler is connected. Essential for older St Helens systems with accumulated sludge and magnetite, which can damage a new heat exchanger within months if not removed.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Gas Safe and Benchmark certificates on the day</strong><p>Legal requirement. Both issued on installation day and sent by email. Required to validate the manufacturer warranty and for landlord compliance.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Manufacturer warranty registered on your behalf</strong><p>We register the warranty with Worcester Bosch or Vaillant on installation day. You receive email confirmation immediately.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Old boiler removed and disposed</strong><p>We remove your old boiler, including the fire surround and hearth where applicable in back boiler replacements. All waste taken away. No skips required.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Full commissioning and demonstration</strong><p>Every radiator balanced, system pressure set, full heating and hot water cycle run. We walk you through the new controls before we leave.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- BRANDS -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Boiler Brands We Install in St Helens</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">We install the four most trusted boiler brands in the UK. All A-rated condensing boilers compliant with Boiler Plus regulations.</p>
